\par - msgtDataReply (*) is similar to msgtData except that the sender does not want an answer from the recipient(s).
\par - msgtDataRaw (*) is used to sent raw bytes to the server without using an internal message header. This flag has to be combined with either msgtData, or msgtDataRequest or msgtDataReply.
\par - msgtWhisper (*) is used to whisper to some channel members instead of 
\par sending the entire channel. The recipients get the whole list of recipients.
