\par }{\cf5 1. ConnectionState
\par }{\tab Name:\tab \tab ConnectionState
\par \tab Type:\tab \tab enumConnectionState
\par \tab Access:\tab \tab Read Only
\par \tab Usage:\tab \tab Returns the current connection state of the control. The enumConnectionState 
\par }\pard \fi720\li1440\nowidctlpar\adjustright {enumeration is made of the following values:
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\adjustright {\tab \tab \tab \tab csDisconnected\tab = 0
\par \tab \tab \tab \tab csConnecting\tab = 1
\par \tab \tab \tab \tab csConnected\tab = 2
\par \tab \tab \tab \tab csLogging\tab = 3
\par \tab \tab \tab \tab csLogged\tab = 4
\par \tab \tab \tab \tab csDisconnecting\tab = 5
\par 
\par \tab Example:
\par \tab \tab \tab }{\cf2 Dim cs As enumConnectionState
\par 
\par \tab \tab \tab cs = MsChatPr1.ConnectionState}{
\par 
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\outlinelevel0\adjustright {\tab Notes:\tab \tab This property is always accessible. After successfully calling the Connect 
\par }\pard \fi720\li1440\nowidctlpar\adjustright {method, the ConnectionState switches from csDisconnected to csConnecting, to 
\par csConnected.
\par After successfully calling the Login method the ConnectionState switches from 
\par }\pard \li2160\nowidctlpar\adjustright {csConnected to csLogging, to csLogged or from csDisconnected to csConnecting, to csLogging, to csLogged.
\par When calling Disconnect, the ConnectionState switches from csConnected to csDisconnecting to csDisconnected or from csLogged to csDisconnecting to csDisconnected.
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\adjustright {\cf5 
\par 
\par 2. ConnectionType
\par }{\tab Name:\tab \tab ConnectionType
\par \tab Type:\tab \tab enumConnectionType
\par \tab Access:\tab \tab Read Only
\par \tab Usage:\tab \tab Returns the type of connection established with the chat server: IRC or IRCX.
